                    <span>On a whim, I paid for rhis movie on pay-per-view.  As I began watching it, I was immediately hooked!  I couldn't stop watching!  This movie made me laugh, it made me cry, it made me want to scream!  Any movie that can make me do all this is worth the money!  I ran out a few days later and purchased this movie for myself.  Now, I watch it about once a month if not more!  If you're like me and enhoy a movie that can pull you into it like you are one of the characters.  You feel the movie in your heart, then you'll love Latter Days!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Questions we all have.. answers that can be many.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
                      /
                      <span>2</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-05-11</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The intriguing thing about this movie is that it doesn't hit you over the head and force you to like it. The dynamics of the characters unfold at just the right pace so the viewer has a chance to disseminate what is going on. Writer/director CJ Cox, drew on personal experiences growing up in the Mormon church to tell this story. I think if he had been Muslin, or Pakistani, he would have used that religion as a basis for the plot. The real irony to this story is how organized religion can be so hateful, bigoted and ignorant that it's ok to for them to be that way as long as they put the lord behind or in front of it.
<br />
<br />I truly enjoyed watching this film, and have watched it several times since. There could have been more depth and dimension to other supporting characters, but I can see that the director didn't want to detract focus away from the main characters. After all it is a two hour movie and not a documentary. Being 19 years old isn't a pre requisite to understanding what this movie is about., I can still relate and appreciate what the story has to offer, which is understanding, compassion, humanity, empathy, self worth & unconditional love. 	
<br />
<br />It can be said that watching this movie can have a  life lesson effect, which can have us searching within ourselves to ask certain questions.. How does my existence fit into the scheme of things? Do I have the capacity of love unconditionally? Am I shallow and ignorant enough to put my needs above someone else that I profess to care about? Can I accept and love myself enough, and believe my self worth? Am I loved by others? We as humans have a tendency to put ourselves on pedestals,  professing at times what great people we are, and all the good we do. The reality is  we gloss over, and at times completely omit certain truths to our darker nature hoping  that the good we do will shift the focus. </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A Really Good Movie</div>
